Greg Fernette - General Manager, Gold and Other Minerals Exploration
Greg began his career in 1968 as a field assistant in Antarctica. Following his graduation in 1972, he has spent the last 35 years exploring for and developing projects in a wide variety of mineral commodities in an equally large number of countries and geological backgrounds. Between 1991- 2001 Greg was Vice President of Watts Griffis and McOuat Limited, managing its Denver office and involved in project work worldwide.  His six years prior to joining Savannah in July 2007 were spent setting up and managing exploration operations for a large American conglomerate in Saudi Arabia.
